I read all the reviews decrying this recipe, and I feel that the first thing that needs to be considered is that it comes from Ligonier, PA--a beautiful city, but not one known for being on the edge culinary concepts. Second, the ingredients are very good, the proportions listed just make it a little bland. I tried the following combo of the same stuff and it was AWESOME--guests were eating it with a spoon: 12 oz. cream cheese; 14 oz. chopped chokes, marinated and drained; 1/2 jalapeno pepper, chopped, seeds and gills removed; 1/3 cup low fat sour cream; 1/4 cup mayonnaise; 1/2 cup parmesean cheese; 1 tbs. worstershire sauce; 1 tablespoon dijon mustard; combine, bake at 400 degrees for 20 mintues, serve it and watch the crowd go wild! So the recipe takes a little alteration, but isn't that what cooking's all about? This is a definite crowd pleaser.

